Steps Involved

Step 1: Using Spring Initializr (via the Web or IDE) configure the project as: 
Project Metadata:
Project Name: BookstoreAPI
Group: com.example.bookstore
Artifact: BookstoreAPI
Packaging: Jar
Java Version: 17 

Step 2: Providing Dependencies:
Spring Web: For creating RESTful web services.
Spring Boot DevTools: To provide automatic restarts and other development-time features.
Lombok: To reduce boilerplate code like getters, setters, and constructors.

What's new in Spring Boot 3?
-Enhanced Observability:
Spring Boot 3 introduces enhancements in observability, including better integration with OpenTelemetry and Micrometer, enabling easier monitoring and tracing.
-Improved Configuration Processing:
Spring Boot 3 includes improvements in configuration processing, making it easier to work with complex configuration properties.
-New AOT (Ahead-of-Time) Compilation:
Spring Boot 3 introduces an AOT engine, which can optimize the application at build time, reducing runtime overhead and improving startup performance.





